    "2 ae higher the remuneration The distinction we speak of is well understood in Italy though it does not appear to be so here where we observe that the highest and the lowest talent meet in these subscriptions for benefits precisely the same amount of encouragement We should be glad to see this mistake rectified and it is not yet too late to correct it in respect to our Prima Donna We republish from the Courier a letter of Mr James Prinseps on the subject of the blowing off in the Forbes he explanations of Mr Prinsep an authority to which every one will bow in matters of science fully acquit the Chief Engineer Mr Dayus of any blame and we therefore hesitate not again to express our regret that we should have passed any censure upon him still more that we should have spoken so harshly as we did at first in our vexation at the deplora bly slow rate of the Forbess progress which it would seem Captain Forth is wrong in ascribing as he has done to the frequent blowing off That operation may be performed we understand without materially if at all impeding the vessels way"
